# Stage 4.5 — reference hardening

## Goal
Strengthen stage 3 and stage 4 using real reference scenario suites already added to the repo.

## Scope in
- New reference-backed tests for:
  - Suite 00 seed blueprints
  - Suite 10 MyOS stage 3 foundations
  - Suite 20 MyOS stage 4 permissions and orchestration
- Small DSL fixes only when the reference suites expose real drift
- Supporting equivalence helpers
- Reference hardening docs

## Scope out
- Stage 5 AI implementation
- Stage 6 PayNote implementation
- Editing pipeline
- Broad refactors unrelated to reference-suite hardening

## Sources of truth
1. `docs/ts-dsl-sdk/reference-suites/**`
2. `docs/ts-dsl-sdk/final-dsl-sdk-mapping-reference.md`
3. `docs/ts-dsl-sdk/complex-flow-materialization-reference.md`
4. Existing stage 3 and stage 4 implementation/tests
5. Java examples only as secondary ergonomic reference

## Behavioral guardrails
- Preserve runtime-correct behavior
- Do not normalize reference docs to current DSL bugs
- Fix the DSL if reference-backed equivalence proves drift
- Any deviation must be documented explicitly

## Output expectations
- New docs under `docs/ts-dsl-sdk/reference-hardening/**`
- New or updated tests in `libs/sdk-dsl`
- Verification commands must pass before claiming completion
